pageContext.claim: “When I look at that catastrophe that took place in Florida where the Republican candidates kept getting less and less and less and less. And fortunately, Rick Scott and Ron ended up winning their election, but it was disgraceful what happened there.”
pageContext.analysis: The president is referring to the long time it took to count votes in Florida's midterm elections. That narrowed the election results in race for governor and senator, as there were more outstanding votes for Democrats than Republicans. But there was no evidence of voter fraud.
